    <title>Creating a new person entity</title>
    <shortdesc>The "Tag Person" option is for tagging people by name. It usually contains a proper
        noun or noun phrase, but can also contain pronouns or other ways of referring to
        someone.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Highlight the text that you would like to tag as a <cmdname>Person</cmdname>.
                    Click on the toolbar or right-click options (see images below).<image
                        placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A3adf859a-d833-4a77-9971-f5c25a9b0dbb/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_t5p_pyw_mp" align="center"/><image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Afe617d28-e61f-484c-91cf-9788eb21517a/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_tkx_blv_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Try to find the person you are tagging in the CWRC or VIAF.<image
                        placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Af2b3f9bf-bee4-41d9-9c94-305cc85d3636/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_mdk_2lv_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>If your entry is not in the CWRC entity lookup system you have the option to
                    create your own. To do this click on "Create New Person" button at the bottom of
                    that page.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>An "Add Person" pop-up appears, fill it out (see note) and click <cmdname>OK</cmdname>.</cmd>
                <info>The only mandatory field is the "Person Name," though there are many other
                    areas that you can fill out.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A261ca7fa-d5cb-47a1-bc26-554d32b75a00/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_epv_rj2_lp" align="center" height="6in" width="4in"/></info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you have created a person entry in the CWRC entity repository, you can now
                    add more information about the tag (precision, person type, etc.). Click on
                    <cmdname>Save</cmdname>.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A2919b272-4c88-47cf-bf7a-cd0bbf9f5587/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_flk_5j2_lp" align="center" height="6in" width="4in"/></cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result>You have now created a new CWRC entity entry, you can use this creation the next
            time that you go to tag this person.<image placement="break"
                href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A1e267644-f1df-4a3a-adec-92f9b460bd6a/datastream/OBJ/view"
                id="image_lvq_xj2_lp" align="center" height="4in" width="6in"/>
